<div class="indented"><a id="comment-13328"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/better-notification-credit-cards#comment-13328" class="active">really a problem?</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="http://www.astro.multivax.de:8000/helbig/helbig.html" rel="nofollow">Phillip Helbig</a> (not verified) on Mon, 2012-01-02 00:23.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>"The whole credit card system is flawed — I just have a number and anybody who gets that number can charge to my account."</p>
<p>If it were really that easy, the system would no longer exist.  Anyone I have ever bought anything with via credit card has my full details.  But mine have never been abused.</p>
<p>AFAIK, unless there is a piece of paper with a signature on it, or unless a PIN was used, when in doubt you can get the money refunded at no charge to you.  If this weren't the case, no-one would use credit cards.  There might be flaws, but this is not one of them.</p>
</div>
